result.execSummary:
The defendant Austin A. Jannette was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: **Total restitution in the amount of $496.75 agreed upon in the stipulation and order filed December 27, 2016. Restitution paid in full - bond previously posted in the amount of $1000 has been applied. Remaining bond applied to costs.**

Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. No contact with J. Langham, Stone Ridge Piggly Wiggly in Wautoma and/or Sentry Foods in Redgranite directly or indirectly. No phone calls, e-mails, text messages, written communications or by third party.

DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.  Defendant is ordered to participate and successfully complete the Waushara County TAD/Safe Streets Program. Defendant to report to the Wautoma Probation & Parole Office by no later than 8:00 a.m. on October 25, 2016.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.
